{
  "text": "Evidence of the permanent activation of CCK2R is rather scarce in the literature. A mis-spliced form of CCK2R retaining intron 4 (corresponding to an insertion of 69 amino acid residues in the middle of intracellular loop 3-ICL3, Figure A1 ) and expressed in stomach, colon, and pancreatic cancers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] has been shown to be more effective compared to the wild type in mobilizing cytosolic calcium expressed in CHO cells [CITATION_4] . The expression of this ICL3-expanded version of CCK2R in Balb3T3 cells was found to result in constitutive CCK2R activation and spontaneous calcium oscillations not blocked by the CCK2R antagonist CAM1028 [CITATION_5] , but such constitutive CCK2R activation and spontaneous calcium oscillations could not be confirmed after expression in CHO cells [CITATION_6] . Another case of constitutively active CCK2R is mutant CCK2R E151A (E151 of the E/DRY motif) accompanied by enhanced cell proliferation and invasion [CITATION_7] , but this mutation (E151A) is obviously not related to the photooxidative activation of CCK2R since the 1 O 2 -susceptible residue Y remains. Future elucidation on the three-dimensional structure of resting and agonist-activated CCK2R may shed light on uncertainties with regard to the atomic details of permanent photooxidative CCK2R activation. Such works might also resolve the difference between reversible and permanent CCK2R activation through agonists or photooxidation, respectively. Evidence of the permanent activation of CCK2R is rather scarce in the literature. A mis-spliced form of CCK2R retaining intron 4 (corresponding to an insertion of 69 amino acid residues in the middle of intracellular loop 3-ICL3, Figure A1 ) and expressed in stomach, colon, and pancreatic cancers [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] has been shown to be more effective compared to the wild type in mobilizing cytosolic calcium expressed in CHO cells [CITATION_11] . The expression of this ICL3-expanded version of CCK2R in Balb3T3 cells was found to result in constitutive CCK2R activation and spontaneous calcium oscillations not blocked by the CCK2R antagonist CAM1028 [CITATION_12] , but such constitutive CCK2R activation and spontaneous calcium oscillations could not be confirmed after expression in CHO cells [CITATION_13] . Another case of constitutively active CCK2R is mutant CCK2R E151A (E151 of the E/DRY motif) accompanied by enhanced cell proliferation and invasion [CITATION_14] , but this mutation (E151A) is obviously not related to the photooxidative activation of CCK2R since the 1 O2-susceptible residue Y remains. Future elucidation on the three-dimensional structure of resting and agonist-activated CCK2R may shed light on uncertainties with regard to the atomic details of permanent photooxidative CCK2R activation. Such works might also resolve the difference between reversible and permanent CCK2R activation through agonists or photooxidation, respectively.",
  "correct_citation": {
